    <div class="jumbotron">
        <h2>Upgrade Strategy</h2>
        <p>The further along in the game that you get, how you upgrade your base will begin to matter.  The general rule of thumb is that you want to be able to 3 star your base,
            which consequently means doing offense 1st.  Offense includes: Army Camps, Spell Factory, Clan Castle, Laboratory upgrades, and heroes.</p>
        <p>Atleast in this clan, I am pretty forgiving if your base has been rushed up to this point, but incorrectly upgraded townhall 9s can spell disaster for war matchups.
            So, as you may have noticed, almost all of the offensive upgrades cost elixir, so what are we to do with our spare gold??? You want to upgrade your existing defenses(wall included) with your spare gold.
        I would suggest atleast getting your army camps, cc, and spell factory upgraded before even thinking about dropping xbows.</p>
    </div> 
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <h2>Farming Strategies</h2>
        <p>Newer players may have a hard time adjusting to these more difficult bases at 1st, so I see a lot of people keeping a war army for farming...THIS IS A TERRIBLE IDEA. I would like to remind everybody
            that trophies don't mean anything, the only thing that matters is loot.  If your trophies get too high, consider dropping them, personally I think crystal 3 is a good place to hang out until you get your base almost maxed.
            I use 2 Strategies for farming:</p>
        <ul>New to Town Hall 9, I used the same strategy that I did at Town Hall 8, filling in extra camp space with archers or goblins</ul>
        <ul>After I got giants, archers, and goblins upgraded => 50 goblins, 1 healer, 10 giants, 126 archers 2 rage 2 heal 1 jump</ul>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/WO3_eo13Tdk">See example here</a><br />
