    <div class="jumbotron">
        <h2>War Strategies</h2>
        <p>There are 3 attacks that I believe will 3 star any Town Hall 9 if executed properly, they are the Lavaloon attack, GOHO(Golem and Hogs), and Queen walk with valks. Troops for all must be max for th9</p>
        <h3>Lavaloon</h3>
        <p>Your army should consist of:</p>
        <ul>3 lavahounds(if xbows are pointed up, otherwise only go with 2)</ul>
        <ul>25 balloons</ul>
        <ul>5 archers</ul>
        <ul>2 Lightning, 1 earthquake, 2 rage, and a donated haste and lavahound</ul>
        <p>2 things to look at when determining attack is troop draw and archer queen position. If the archer queen is exposed, take her out with your king</p>
        <p>You want to lightning out air defense that is closest to your point of entry to drawing troops out</p>
        <p>Send 2 lavahounds at 2 of the remaining air defenses with balloons divided equally among them</p>
        <p>Drop balloons 1st, then lavahounds after, try and send the max cc hound at air defense that is by the enemy queen and drop a rage on it as it is bursting</p><br/>
        <h3>GOHO</h3>
        <p>Your army should consist of:</p>
        <ul>1 golem</ul>
        <ul>30 Hogs</ul>
        <ul>8 wizards</ul>
        <ul>4 wallbreakers</ul>
        <ul>3 Heal, 1 jump, 1 poison, CC Golem and poison</ul>
        <p>Your golems, wizards and heroes will serve as a "kill squad", the goals of which is to take out 1 or both enemy heroes, kill enemy cc, and set off big bombs</p>
        <p>Wall break into outer layer of base and then use the jump spell to allow kill squad access to the core of the base</p>
        <p>Surgically deploy your hogs along the other side of the base dropping heals as you see fit</p>
    </div>
</div>


